rver\" package decreases the risk of the\naccidental (or intentional) activation of tftp services.","gid":"V-38606","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095","rule_id":"SV-50407r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000222","cci_ref":["CCI-000381"],"nist":"CM-7 a Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if the \"tftp-server\"\npackage is installed:\n\n# rpm -q tftp-server\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"tftp-server\" package can be removed with the following\ncommand:\n\n# yum erase tftp-server","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package tftp-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package tftp-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38622":{"vuln_num":"V-38622","rule_title":"Mail relaying must be restricted.","vuln_discuss":"This ensures \"postfix\" accepts mail messages (such as cron job\nreports) from the local system only, and not from the network, which protects\nit from network attack.","gid":"V-38622","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50423r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000249","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"If the system is an authorized mail relay host, this is not\napplicable.\n\nRun the following command to ensure postfix accepts mail messages from only the\nlocal system:\n\n$ grep inet_interfaces /etc/postfix/main.cf\n\nIf properly configured, the output should show only \"localhost\".\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"Edit the file \"/etc/postfix/main.cf\" to ensure that only the\nfollowing \"inet_interfaces\" line appears:\n\ninet_interfaces = localhost","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/postfix/main.cf content should match /^[\\s]*inet_interfaces[\\s]*=[\\s]*localhost[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/postfix/main.cf content should match /^[\\s]*inet_interfaces[\\s]*=[\\s]*localhost[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38451":{"vuln_num":"V-38451","rule_title":"The /etc/passwd file must be group-owned by root.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/passwd\" file contains information about the users that are\nconfigured on the system. Protection of this file is critical for system\nsecurity.","gid":"V-38451","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50251r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000040","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the group ownership of \"/etc/passwd\", run the\ncommand:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/passwd\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following group-owner.\n\"root\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the group owner of \"/etc/passwd\", run the\ncommand:\n\n# chgrp root /etc/passwd","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd gid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd gid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38511":{"vuln_num":"V-38511","rule_title":"IP forwarding for IPv4 must not be enabled, unless the system is a\nrouter.","vuln_discuss":"IP forwarding permits the kernel to forward packets from one network\ninterface to another. The ability to forward packets between two networks is\nonly appropriate for systems acting as routers.","gid":"V-38511","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50312r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000082","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"The status of the \"net.ipv4.ip_forward\" kernel parameter can\nbe queried by running the following command:\n\n$ sysctl net.ipv4.ip_forward\n\nThe output of the command should indicate a value of \"0\". If this value is\nnot the default value, investigate how it could have been adjusted at runtime,\nand verify it is not set improperly in \"/etc/sysctl.conf\".\n\n$ grep net.ipv4.ip_forward /etc/sysctl.conf\n\nThe ability to forward packets is only appropriate for routers. If the correct\nvalue is not returned, this is a finding. ","fix_text":"To set the runtime status of the \"net.ipv4.ip_forward\" kernel\nparameter, run the following command:\n\n# sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=0\n\nIf this is not the system's default value, add the following line to\n\"/etc/sysctl.conf\":\n\nnet.ipv4.ip_forward = 0","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.ip_forward value should not be nil\n","PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.ip_forward value should eq 0\n","PASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.ip_forward[\\s]*=[\\s]*0[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.ip_forward value should not be nil\nPASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.ip_forward value should eq 0\nPASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.ip_forward[\\s]*=[\\s]*0[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38680":{"vuln_num":"V-38680","rule_title":"The audit system must identify staff members to receive notifications\nof audit log storage volume capacity issues.","vuln_discuss":"Email sent to the root account is typically aliased to the\nadministrators of the system, who can take appropriate action.","gid":"V-38680","group_title":"SRG-OS-000046","rule_id":"SV-50481r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000313","cci_ref":["CCI-000139"],"nist":"AU-5 a Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" and locate the following\nline to determine if the system is configured to send email to an account when\nit needs to notify an administrator:\n\naction_mail_acct = root\n\n\nIf auditd is not configured to send emails per identified actions, this is a\nfinding.","fix_text":"The \"auditd\" service can be configured to send email to a\ndesignated account in certain situations. Add or correct the following line in\n\"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" to ensure that administrators are notified via email\nfor those situations:\n\naction_mail_acct = root","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^action_mail_acct\\s*=\\s*(\\S+)\\s*$/\n","PASS -- root should eq \"root\"\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^action_mail_acct\\s*=\\s*(\\S+)\\s*$/\nPASS -- root should eq \"root\"\n"},"V-38587":{"vuln_num":"V-38587","rule_title":"The telnet-server package must not be installed.","vuln_discuss":"Removing the \"telnet-server\" package decreases the risk of the\nunencrypted telnet service's accidental (or intentional) activation.\n\n    Mitigation:  If the telnet-server package is configured to only allow\nencrypted sessions, such as with Kerberos or the use of encrypted network\ntunnels, the risk of exposing sensitive information is mitigated.","gid":"V-38587","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095","rule_id":"SV-50388r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000206","cci_ref":["CCI-000381"],"nist":"CM-7 a Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if the \"telnet-server\"\npackage is installed:\n\n# rpm -q telnet-server\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"telnet-server\" package can be uninstalled with the\nfollowing command:\n\n# yum erase telnet-server","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package telnet-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package telnet-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38636":{"vuln_num":"V-38636","rule_title":"The system must retain enough rotated audit logs to cover the required\nlog retention period.","vuln_discuss":"The total storage for audit log files must be large enough to retain\nlog information over the period required. This is a function of the maximum log\nfile size and the number of logs retained.","gid":"V-38636","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50437r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000159","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" and locate the following\nline to determine how many logs the system is configured to retain after\nrotation: \"# grep num_logs /etc/audit/auditd.conf\"\n\nnum_logs = 5\n\n\nIf the overall system log file(s) retention hasn't been properly set up, this\nis a finding.","fix_text":"Determine how many log files \"auditd\" should retain when it\nrotates logs. Edit the file \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\". Add or modify the\nfollowing line, substituting [NUMLOGS] with the correct value:\n\nnum_logs = [NUMLOGS]\n\nSet the value to 5 for general-purpose systems. Note that values less than 2\nresult in no log rotation.","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^num_logs\\s*=\\s*(\\d+)\\s*$/\n","PASS -- 5 should cmp >= 5\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^num_logs\\s*=\\s*(\\d+)\\s*$/\nPASS -- 5 should cmp >= 5\n"},"V-38602":{"vuln_num":"V-38602","rule_title":"The rlogind service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"The rlogin service uses unencrypted network communications, which\nmeans that data from the login session, including passwords and all other\ninformation transmitted during the session, can be stolen by eavesdroppers on\nthe network.","gid":"V-38602","group_title":"SRG-OS-000248","rule_id":"SV-50403r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000218","cci_ref":["CCI-001436"],"nist":"AC-17 (8) Rev_4","check_content":"\nTo check that the \"rlogin\" service is disabled in system boot configuration,\nrun the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"rlogin\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"rlogin\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"rlogin\" --list\nrlogin off\nOR\nerror reading information on service rlogin: No such file or directory\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"rlogin\" service, which is available with the\n\"rsh-server\" package and runs as a service through xinetd, should be\ndisabled. The \"rlogin\" service can be disabled with the following command:\n\n# chkconfig rlogin off","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38461":{"vuln_num":"V-38461","rule_title":"The /etc/group file must have mode 0644 or less permissive.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/group\" file contains information regarding groups that are\nconfigured on the system. Protection of this file is important for system\nsecurity.","gid":"V-38461","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50261r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000044","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the permissions of \"/etc/group\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/group\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following permissions:\n\"-rw-r--r--\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the permissions of \"/etc/group\", run the\ncommand:\n\n# chmod 644 /etc/group","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/group should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should not be writable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should not be writable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/group should be writable by owner\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/group should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/group should not be writable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/group should not be writable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/group should not be executable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/group should be readable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/group should be writable by owner\n"},"V-38677":{"vuln_num":"V-38677","rule_title":"The NFS server must not have the insecure file locking option enabled.","vuln_discuss":"Allowing insecure file locking could allow for sensitive data to be\nviewed or edited by an unauthorized user.","gid":"V-38677","group_title":"SRG-OS-000104","rule_id":"SV-50478r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000309","cci_ref":["CCI-000764"],"nist":"IA-2 Rev_4","check_content":"To verify insecure file locking has been disabled, run the\nfollowing command:\n\n# grep insecure_locks /etc/exports\n\n\nIf there is output, this is a finding.","fix_text":"By default the NFS server requires secure file-lock requests,\nwhich require credentials from the client in order to lock a file. Most NFS\nclients send credentials with file lock requests, however, there are a few\nclients that do not send credentials when requesting a file-lock, allowing the\nclient to only be able to lock world-readable files. To get around this, the\n\"insecure_locks\" option can be used so these clients can access the desired\nexport. This poses a security risk by potentially allowing the client access to\ndata for which it does not have authorization. Remove any instances of the\n\"insecure_locks\" option from the file \"/etc/exports\".","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/exports content should not match /^[^#]*insecure_locks.*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/exports content should not match /^[^#]*insecure_locks.*$/\n"},"V-38544":{"vuln_num":"V-38544","rule_title":"The system must use a reverse-path filter for IPv4 network traffic\nwhen possible by default.","vuln_discuss":"Enabling reverse path filtering drops packets with source addresses\nthat should not have been able to be received on the interface they were\nreceived on. It should not be used on systems which are routers for complicated\nnetworks, but is helpful for end hosts and routers serving small networks.","gid":"V-38544","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50345r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000097","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"The status of the \"net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter\" kernel\nparameter can be queried by running the following command:\n\n$ sysctl net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter\n\nThe output of the command should indicate a value of \"1\". If this value is\nnot the default value, investigate how it could have been adjusted at runtime,\nand verify it is not set improperly in \"/etc/sysctl.conf\".\n\n$ grep net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter /etc/sysctl.conf\n\nIf the correct value is not returned, this is a finding. ","fix_text":"To set the runtime status of the\n\"net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter\" kernel parameter, run the following\ncommand:\n\n# sysctl -w net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter=1\n\nIf this is not the system's default value, add the following line to\n\"/etc/sysctl.conf\":\n\nnet.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter = 1","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter value should not be nil\n","PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter value should eq 1\n","PASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter[\\s]*=[\\s]*1[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter value should not be nil\nPASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter value should eq 1\nPASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.conf.default.rp_filter[\\s]*=[\\s]*1[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38504":{"vuln_num":"V-38504","rule_title":"The /etc/shadow file must have mode 0000.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/shadow\" file contains the list of local system accounts\nand stores password hashes. Protection of this file is critical for system\nsecurity. Failure to give ownership of this file to root provides the\ndesignated owner with access to sensitive information which could weaken the\nsystem security posture.","gid":"V-38504","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50305r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000035","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the permissions of \"/etc/shadow\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/shadow\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following permissions:\n\"----------\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the permissions of \"/etc/shadow\", run the\ncommand:\n\n# chmod 0000 /etc/shadow","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow gid should cmp == 0\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be setgid\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be sticky\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be setuid\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow uid should cmp == 0\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by owner\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow gid should cmp == 0\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be setgid\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be sticky\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be setuid\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be executable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be readable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow uid should cmp == 0\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow should not be writable by owner\n"},"V-38483":{"vuln_num":"V-38483","rule_title":"The system package management tool must cryptographically verify the\nauthenticity of system software packages during installation.","vuln_discuss":"Ensuring the validity of packages' cryptographic signatures prior to\ninstallation ensures the provenance of the software and protects against\nmalicious tampering.","gid":"V-38483","group_title":"SRG-OS-000103","rule_id":"SV-50283r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000013","cci_ref":["CCI-000663"],"nist":"SA-7 Rev_4","check_content":"To determine whether \"yum\" is configured to use \"gpgcheck\",\ninspect \"/etc/yum.conf\" and ensure the following appears in the \"[main]\"\nsection:\n\ngpgcheck=1\n\nA value of \"1\" indicates that \"gpgcheck\" is enabled. Absence of a\n\"gpgcheck\" line or a setting of \"0\" indicates that it is disabled.\nIf GPG checking is not enabled, this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"yum\" system package management tool is not used to update the system,\nverify with the SA that installed packages are cryptographically signed.","fix_text":"The \"gpgcheck\" option should be used to ensure checking of an\nRPM package's signature always occurs prior to its installation. To configure\nyum to check package signatures before installing them, ensure the following\nline appears in \"/etc/yum.conf\" in the \"[main]\" section:\n\ngpgcheck=1","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/yum.conf content should match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*1\\s*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/yum.conf content should match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*1\\s*$/\n"},"V-38603":{"vuln_num":"V-38603","rule_title":"The ypserv package must not be installed.","vuln_discuss":"Removing the \"ypserv\" package decreases the risk of the accidental\n(or intentional) activation of NIS or NIS+ services.","gid":"V-38603","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095","rule_id":"SV-50404r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000220","cci_ref":["CCI-000381"],"nist":"CM-7 a Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if the \"ypserv\"\npackage is installed:\n\n# rpm -q ypserv\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"ypserv\" package can be uninstalled with the following\ncommand:\n\n# yum erase ypserv","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package ypserv should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package ypserv should not be installed\n"},"V-38582":{"vuln_num":"V-38582","rule_title":"The xinetd service must be disabled if no network services utilizing\nit are enabled.","vuln_discuss":"The xinetd service provides a dedicated listener service for some\nprograms, which is no longer necessary for commonly-used network services.\nDisabling it ensures that these uncommon services are not running, and also\nprevents attacks against xinetd itself.","gid":"V-38582","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50383r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000203","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"If network services are using the xinetd service, this is not\napplicable.\n\nTo check that the \"xinetd\" service is disabled in system boot configuration,\nrun the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"xinetd\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"xinetd\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"xinetd\" --list\n\"xinetd\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"xinetd\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service xinetd status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\nxinetd is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"xinetd\" service can be disabled with the following\ncommands:\n\n# chkconfig xinetd off\n# service xinetd stop","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package xinetd should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package xinetd should not be installed\n"},"V-38642":{"vuln_num":"V-38642","rule_title":"The system default umask for daemons must be 027 or 022.","vuln_discuss":"The umask influences the permissions assigned to files created by a\nprocess at run time. An unnecessarily permissive umask could result in files\nbeing created with insecure permissions.","gid":"V-38642","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50443r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000346","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the value of the \"umask\", run the following command:\n\n$ grep umask /etc/init.d/functions\n\nThe output should show either \"022\" or \"027\".\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The file \"/etc/init.d/functions\" includes initialization\nparameters for most or all daemons started at boot time. The default umask of\n022 prevents creation of group- or world-writable files. To set the default\numask for daemons, edit the following line, inserting 022 or 027 for [UMASK]\nappropriately:\n\numask [UMASK]\n\nSetting the umask to too restrictive a setting can cause serious errors at\nruntime. Many daemons on the system already individually restrict themselves to\na umask of 077 in their own init scripts.","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/rc.d/init.d/functions content should match /^\\s*umask\\s+([^#\\s]*)/\n","PASS -- 022 should match /^0?(022|027)$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/rc.d/init.d/functions content should match /^\\s*umask\\s+([^#\\s]*)/\nPASS -- 022 should match /^0?(022|027)$/\n"},"V-51369":{"vuln_num":"V-51369","rule_title":"The system must use a Linux Security Module configured to limit the\nprivileges of system services.","vuln_discuss":"Setting the SELinux policy to \"targeted\" or a more specialized\npolicy ensures the system will confine processes that are likely to be targeted\nfor exploitation, such as network or system services.","gid":"V-51369","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-65579r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000023","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Check the file \"/etc/selinux/config\" and ensure the following\nline appears:\n\nSELINUXTYPE=targeted\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding. ","fix_text":"The SELinux \"targeted\" policy is appropriate for\ngeneral-purpose desktops and servers, as well as systems in many other roles.\nTo configure the system to use this policy, add or correct the following line\nin \"/etc/selinux/config\":\n\nSELINUXTYPE=targeted\n\nOther policies, such as \"mls\", provide additional security labeling and\ngreater confinement but are not compatible with many general-purpose use cases.\n","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/selinux/config content should match /^[\\s]*SELINUXTYPE[\\s]*=[\\s]*([^\\s]*)/\n","PASS -- targeted should eq \"targeted\"\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/selinux/config content should match /^[\\s]*SELINUXTYPE[\\s]*=[\\s]*([^\\s]*)/\nPASS -- targeted should eq \"targeted\"\n"},"V-38676":{"vuln_num":"V-38676","rule_title":"The xorg-x11-server-common (X Windows) package must not be installed,\nunless required.","vuln_discuss":"Unnecessary packages should not be installed to decrease the attack\nsurface of the system.","gid":"V-38676","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50477r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000291","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To ensure the X Windows package group is removed, run the\nfollowing command:\n\n$ rpm -qi xorg-x11-server-common\n\nThe output should be:\n\npackage xorg-x11-server-common is not installed\n\n\nIf it is not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"Removing all packages which constitute the X Window System\nensures users or malicious software cannot start X. To do so, run the following\ncommand:\n\n# yum groupremove \"X Window System\"","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package xorg-x11-server-common should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package xorg-x11-server-common should not be installed\n"},"V-38627":{"vuln_num":"V-38627","rule_title":"The openldap-servers package must not be installed unless required.","vuln_discuss":"Unnecessary packages should not be installed to decrease the attack\nsurface of the system.","gid":"V-38627","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50428r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000256","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To verify the \"openldap-servers\" package is not installed,\nrun the following command:\n\n$ rpm -q openldap-servers\n\nThe output should show the following.\n\npackage openldap-servers is not installed\n\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"openldap-servers\" package should be removed if not in use.\n\n# yum erase openldap-servers\n\nThe openldap-servers RPM is not installed by default on RHEL6 machines. It is\nneeded only by the OpenLDAP server, not by the clients which use LDAP for\nauthentication. If the system is not intended for use as an LDAP Server it\nshould be removed.","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package openldap-servers should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package openldap-servers should not be installed\n"},"V-38487":{"vuln_num":"V-38487","rule_title":"The system package management tool must cryptographically verify the\nauthenticity of all software packages during installation.","vuln_discuss":"Ensuring all packages' cryptographic signatures are valid prior to\ninstallation ensures the provenance of the software and protects against\nmalicious tampering.","gid":"V-38487","group_title":"SRG-OS-000103","rule_id":"SV-50288r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000015","cci_ref":["CCI-000663"],"nist":"SA-7 Rev_4","check_content":"To determine whether \"yum\" has been configured to disable\n\"gpgcheck\" for any repos, inspect all files in \"/etc/yum.repos.d\" and\nensure the following does not appear in any sections:\n\ngpgcheck=0\n\nA value of \"0\" indicates that \"gpgcheck\" has been disabled for that repo.\nIf GPG checking is disabled, this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"yum\" system package management tool is not used to update the system,\nverify with the SA that installed packages are cryptographically signed.","fix_text":"To ensure signature checking is not disabled for any repos,\nremove any lines from files in \"/etc/yum.repos.d\" of the form:\n\ngpgcheck=0","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Vault.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n","PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Media.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n","PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Base.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n","PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-fasttrack.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n","PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Debuginfo.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Vault.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\nPASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Media.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\nPASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Base.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\nPASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-fasttrack.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\nPASS -- File /etc/yum.repos.d/CentOS-Debuginfo.repo content should not match /^\\s*gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*0\\s*$/\n"},"V-38656":{"vuln_num":"V-38656","rule_title":"The system must use SMB client signing for connecting to samba servers\nusing smbclient.","vuln_discuss":"Packet signing can prevent man-in-the-middle attacks which modify SMB\npackets in transit.","gid":"V-38656","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50457r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000272","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To verify that Samba clients running smbclient must use packet\nsigning, run the following command:\n\n# grep signing /etc/samba/smb.conf\n\nThe output should show:\n\nclient signing = mandatory\n\n\nIf it is not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To require samba clients running \"smbclient\" to use packet\nsigning, add the following to the \"[global]\" section of the Samba\nconfiguration file in \"/etc/samba/smb.conf\":\n\nclient signing = mandatory\n\nRequiring samba clients such as \"smbclient\" to use packet signing ensures\nthey can only communicate with servers that support packet signing.","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package samba-common should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package samba-common should not be installed\n"},"V-38500":{"vuln_num":"V-38500","rule_title":"The root account must be the only account having a UID of 0.","vuln_discuss":"An account has root authority if it has a UID of 0. Multiple accounts\nwith a UID of 0 afford more opportunity for potential intruders to guess a\npassword for a privileged account. Proper configuration of sudo is recommended\nto afford multiple system administrators access to root privileges in an\naccountable manner.","gid":"V-38500","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50301r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000032","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To list all password file entries for accounts with UID 0, run\nthe following command:\n\n# awk -F: '($3 == 0) {print}' /etc/passwd\n\nThis should print only one line, for the user root.\nIf any account other than root has a UID of 0, this is a finding.","fix_text":"If any account other than root has a UID of 0, this\nmisconfiguration should be investigated and the accounts other than root should\nbe removed or have their UID changed.","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/passwd content should not match /^(?!root:)[^:]*:[^:]:0/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/passwd content should not match /^(?!root:)[^:]*:[^:]:0/\n"},"V-38633":{"vuln_num":"V-38633","rule_title":"The system must set a maximum audit log file size.","vuln_discuss":"The total storage for audit log files must be large enough to retain\nlog information over the period required. This is a function of the maximum log\nfile size and the number of logs retained.","gid":"V-38633","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50434r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000160","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" and locate the following\nline to determine how much data the system will retain in each audit log file:\n\"# grep max_log_file /etc/audit/auditd.conf\"\n\nmax_log_file = 6\n\n\nIf the system audit data threshold hasn't been properly set up, this is a\nfinding.","fix_text":"Determine the amount of audit data (in megabytes) which should be\nretained in each log file. Edit the file \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\". Add or\nmodify the following line, substituting the correct value for [STOREMB]:\n\nmax_log_file = [STOREMB]\n\nSet the value to \"6\" (MB) or higher for general-purpose systems. Larger\nvalues, of course, support retention of even more audit data.","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^max_log_file\\s*=\\s*(\\d+)\\s*$/\n","PASS -- 6 should cmp >= 6\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^max_log_file\\s*=\\s*(\\d+)\\s*$/\nPASS -- 6 should cmp >= 6\n"},"V-38672":{"vuln_num":"V-38672","rule_title":"The netconsole service must be disabled unless required.","vuln_discuss":"The \"netconsole\" service is not necessary unless there is a need to\ndebug kernel panics, which is not common.","gid":"V-38672","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50473r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000289","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"netconsole\" service is disabled in system\nboot configuration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"netconsole\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"netconsole\" service has either not been\ninstalled, or has been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example\nbelow:\n\n# chkconfig \"netconsole\" --list\n\"netconsole\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"netconsole\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service netconsole status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\nnetconsole is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"netconsole\" service is responsible for loading the\nnetconsole kernel module, which logs kernel printk messages over UDP to a\nsyslog server. This allows debugging of problems where disk logging fails and\nserial consoles are impractical. The \"netconsole\" service can be disabled\nwith the following commands:\n\n# chkconfig netconsole off\n# service netconsole stop","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 0 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 1 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 2 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 3 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 4 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 5 should not be enabled\n","PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 6 should not be enabled\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 0 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 1 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 2 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 3 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 4 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 5 should not be enabled\nPASS -- Service netconsole runlevels 6 should not be enabled\n"},"V-38450":{"vuln_num":"V-38450","rule_title":"The /etc/passwd file must be owned by root.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/passwd\" file contains information about the users that are\nconfigured on the system. Protection of this file is critical for system\nsecurity.","gid":"V-38450","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50250r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000039","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the ownership of \"/etc/passwd\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/passwd\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following owner:\n\"root\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the owner of \"/etc/passwd\", run the command:\n\n# chown root /etc/passwd","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd uid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd uid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38646":{"vuln_num":"V-38646","rule_title":"The oddjobd service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"The \"oddjobd\" service may provide necessary functionality in some\nenvironments but it can be disabled if it is not needed. Execution of tasks by\nprivileged programs, on behalf of unprivileged ones, has traditionally been a\nsource of privilege escalation security issues.","gid":"V-38646","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50447r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000266","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"oddjobd\" service is disabled in system\nboot configuration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"oddjobd\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"oddjobd\" service has either not been installed,\nor has been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"oddjobd\" --list\n\"oddjobd\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"oddjobd\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service oddjobd status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\noddjobd is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"oddjobd\" service exists to provide an interface and access\ncontrol mechanism through which specified privileged tasks can run tasks for\nunprivileged client applications. Communication with \"oddjobd\" is through the\nsystem message bus. The \"oddjobd\" service can be disabled with the following\ncommands:\n\n# chkconfig oddjobd off\n# service oddjobd stop","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package oddjob should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package oddjob should not be installed\n"},"V-54381":{"vuln_num":"V-54381","rule_title":"The audit system must switch the system to single-user mode when\navailable audit storage volume becomes dangerously low.","vuln_discuss":"Administrators should be made aware of an inability to record audit\nrecords. If a separate partition or logical volume of adequate size is used,\nrunning low on space for audit records should never occur.","gid":"V-54381","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-68627r3_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000163","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\" and locate the following\nline to determine if the system is configured to either suspend, switch to\nsingle-user mode, or halt when disk space has run low:\n\nadmin_space_left_action = single\n\nIf the system is not configured to switch to single-user mode, suspend, or halt\nfor corrective action, this is a finding. ","fix_text":"The \"auditd\" service can be configured to take an action when\ndisk space is running low but prior to running out of space completely. Edit\nthe file \"/etc/audit/auditd.conf\". Add or modify the following line,\nsubstituting [ACTION] appropriately:\n\nadmin_space_left_action = [ACTION]\n\nSet this value to \"single\" to cause the system to switch to single-user mode\nfor corrective action. Acceptable values also include \"suspend\" and \"halt\".\nFor certain systems, the need for availability outweighs the need to log all\nactions, and a different setting should be determined. Details regarding all\npossible values for [ACTION] are described in the \"auditd.conf\" man page. ","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^\\s*admin_space_left_action[ ]+=[ ]+(\\S+)\\s*$/\n","PASS -- SUSPEND should match /^(?:[sS][iI][nN][gG][lL][eE]|[sS][uU][sS][pP][eE][nN][dD]|[hH][aA][lL][tT])$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/audit/auditd.conf content should match /^\\s*admin_space_left_action[ ]+=[ ]+(\\S+)\\s*$/\nPASS -- SUSPEND should match /^(?:[sS][iI][nN][gG][lL][eE]|[sS][uU][sS][pP][eE][nN][dD]|[hH][aA][lL][tT])$/\n"},"V-38591":{"vuln_num":"V-38591","rule_title":"The rsh-server package must not be installed.","vuln_discuss":"The \"rsh-server\" package provides several obsolete and insecure\nnetwork services. Removing it decreases the risk of those services' accidental\n(or intentional) activation.","gid":"V-38591","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095","rule_id":"SV-50392r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000213","cci_ref":["CCI-000381"],"nist":"CM-7 a Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if the \"rsh-server\"\npackage is installed:\n\n# rpm -q rsh-server\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"rsh-server\" package can be uninstalled with the following\ncommand:\n\n# yum erase rsh-server","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38480":{"vuln_num":"V-38480","rule_title":"Users must be warned 7 days in advance of password expiration.","vuln_discuss":"Setting the password warning age enables users to make the change at a\npractical time.","gid":"V-38480","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50280r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000054","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the password warning age, run the command:\n\n$ grep PASS_WARN_AGE /etc/login.defs\n\nThe DoD requirement is 7.\nIf it is not set to the required value, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To specify how many days prior to password expiration that a\nwarning will be issued to users, edit the file \"/etc/login.defs\" and add or\ncorrect the following line, replacing [DAYS] appropriately:\n\nPASS_WARN_AGE [DAYS]\n\nThe DoD requirement is 7.","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*PASS_WARN_AGE[\\s]*(\\d+)\\s*$/\n","PASS -- 7 should cmp >= 7\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*PASS_WARN_AGE[\\s]*(\\d+)\\s*$/\nPASS -- 7 should cmp >= 7\n"},"V-38473":{"vuln_num":"V-38473","rule_title":"The system must use a separate file system for user home directories.","vuln_discuss":"Ensuring that \"/home\" is mounted on its own partition enables the\nsetting of more restrictive mount options, and also helps ensure that users\ncannot trivially fill partitions used for log or audit data storage.","gid":"V-38473","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50273r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000007","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if \"/home\" is on its\nown partition or logical volume:\n\n$ mount | grep \"on /home \"\n\nIf \"/home\" has its own partition or volume group, a line will be returned.\nIf no line is returned, this is a finding.","fix_text":"If user home directories will be stored locally, create a\nseparate partition for \"/home\" at installation time (or migrate it later\nusing LVM). If \"/home\" will be mounted from another system such as an NFS\nserver, then creating a separate partition is not necessary at installation\ntime, and the mountpoint can instead be configured later.","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- Mount /home should be mounted\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- Mount /home should be mounted\n"},"V-38641":{"vuln_num":"V-38641","rule_title":"The atd service must be disabled.","vuln_discuss":"The \"atd\" service could be used by an unsophisticated insider to\ncarry out activities outside of a normal login session, which could complicate\naccountability. Furthermore, the need to schedule tasks with \"at\" or\n\"batch\" is not common.","gid":"V-38641","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50442r3_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000262","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"If the system requires the use of the \"atd\" service to\nsupport an organizational requirement, this is not applicable.\n\nTo check that the \"atd\" service is disabled in system boot configuration, run\nthe following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"atd\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"atd\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"atd\" --list\n\"atd\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"atd\" is disabled through current runtime\nconfiguration:\n\n# service atd status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\natd is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"at\" and \"batch\" commands can be used to schedule tasks\nthat are meant to be executed only once. This allows delayed execution in a\nmanner similar to cron, except that it is not recurring. The daemon \"atd\"\nkeeps track of tasks scheduled via \"at\" and \"batch\", and executes them at\nthe specified time. The \"atd\" service can be disabled with the following\ncommands:\n\n# chkconfig atd off\n# service atd stop","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package at should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package at should not be installed\n"},"V-38701":{"vuln_num":"V-38701","rule_title":"The TFTP daemon must operate in secure mode which provides access only\nto a single directory on the host file system.","vuln_discuss":"Using the \"-s\" option causes the TFTP service to only serve files\nfrom the given directory. Serving files from an intentionally specified\ndirectory reduces the risk of sharing files which should remain private.","gid":"V-38701","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50502r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000338","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Verify \"tftp\" is configured by with the \"-s\" option by\nrunning the following command:\n\ngrep \"server_args\" /etc/xinetd.d/tftp\n\nThe output should indicate the \"server_args\" variable is configured with the\n\"-s\" flag, matching the example below:\n\n# grep \"server_args\" /etc/xinetd.d/tftp\nserver_args = -s /var/lib/tftpboot\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"If running the \"tftp\" service is necessary, it should be\nconfigured to change its root directory at startup. To do so, ensure\n\"/etc/xinetd.d/tftp\" includes \"-s\" as a command line argument, as shown in\nthe following example (which is also the default):\n\nserver_args = -s /var/lib/tftpboot","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package tftp-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package tftp-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38581":{"vuln_num":"V-38581","rule_title":"The system boot loader configuration file(s) must be group-owned by\nroot.","vuln_discuss":"The \"root\" group is a highly-privileged group. Furthermore, the\ngroup-owner of this file should not have any access privileges anyway.","gid":"V-38581","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50382r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000066","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the group ownership of \"/boot/grub/grub.conf\", run\nthe command:\n\n$ ls -lL /boot/grub/grub.conf\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the group-owner is \"root\".\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The file \"/boot/grub/grub.conf\" should be group-owned by the\n\"root\" group to prevent destruction or modification of the file. To properly\nset the group owner of \"/boot/grub/grub.conf\", run the command:\n\n# chgrp root /boot/grub/grub.conf","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /boot/grub/grub.conf should exist\n","PASS -- File /boot/grub/grub.conf gid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /boot/grub/grub.conf should exist\nPASS -- File /boot/grub/grub.conf gid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38457":{"vuln_num":"V-38457","rule_title":"The /etc/passwd file must have mode 0644 or less permissive.","vuln_discuss":"If the \"/etc/passwd\" file is writable by a group-owner or the world\nthe risk of its compromise is increased. The file contains the list of accounts\non the system and associated information, and protection of this file is\ncritical for system security.","gid":"V-38457","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50257r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000041","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the permissions of \"/etc/passwd\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/passwd\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following permissions:\n\"-rw-r--r--\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the permissions of \"/etc/passwd\", run the\ncommand:\n\n# chmod 0644 /etc/passwd","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd gid should cmp == 0\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be writable by group\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be writable by other\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be setgid\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be sticky\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be setuid\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by owner\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd uid should cmp == 0\n","PASS -- File /etc/passwd should be writable by owner\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/passwd should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd gid should cmp == 0\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be writable by group\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be writable by other\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be setgid\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be sticky\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be setuid\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should not be executable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should be readable by owner\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd uid should cmp == 0\nPASS -- File /etc/passwd should be writable by owner\n"},"V-38604":{"vuln_num":"V-38604","rule_title":"The ypbind service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"Disabling the \"ypbind\" service ensures the system is not acting as a\nclient in a NIS or NIS+ domain.","gid":"V-38604","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50405r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000221","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"ypbind\" service is disabled in system boot\nconfiguration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"ypbind\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"ypbind\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"ypbind\" --list\n\"ypbind\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"ypbind\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service ypbind status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\nypbind is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"ypbind\" service, which allows the system to act as a\nclient in a NIS or NIS+ domain, should be disabled. The \"ypbind\" service can\nbe disabled with the following commands:\n\n# chkconfig ypbind off\n# service ypbind stop","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package ypbind should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package ypbind should not be installed\n"},"V-38503":{"vuln_num":"V-38503","rule_title":"The /etc/shadow file must be group-owned by root.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/shadow\" file stores password hashes. Protection of this\nfile is critical for system security.","gid":"V-38503","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50304r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000034","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the group ownership of \"/etc/shadow\", run the\ncommand:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/shadow\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following group-owner.\n\"root\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the group owner of \"/etc/shadow\", run the\ncommand:\n\n# chgrp root /etc/shadow","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow gid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow gid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38443":{"vuln_num":"V-38443","rule_title":"The /etc/gshadow file must be owned by root.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/gshadow\" file contains group password hashes. Protection\nof this file is critical for system security.","gid":"V-38443","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50243r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000036","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the ownership of \"/etc/gshadow\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/gshadow\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following owner:\n\"root\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the owner of \"/etc/gshadow\", run the command:\n\n# chown root /etc/gshadow","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/gshadow should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/gshadow uid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/gshadow should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/gshadow uid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38671":{"vuln_num":"V-38671","rule_title":"The sendmail package must be removed.","vuln_discuss":"The sendmail software was not developed with security in mind and its\ndesign prevents it from being effectively contained by SELinux. Postfix should\nbe used instead.","gid":"V-38671","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50472r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000288","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine if the \"sendmail\"\npackage is installed:\n\n# rpm -q sendmail\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"Sendmail is not the default mail transfer agent and is not\ninstalled by default. The \"sendmail\" package can be removed with the\nfollowing command:\n\n# yum erase sendmail","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package sendmail should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package sendmail should not be installed\n"},"V-38576":{"vuln_num":"V-38576","rule_title":"The system must use a FIPS 140-2 approved cryptographic hashing\nalgorithm for generating account password hashes (login.defs).","vuln_discuss":"Using a stronger hashing algorithm makes password cracking attacks\nmore difficult.","gid":"V-38576","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120","rule_id":"SV-50377r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000063","cci_ref":["CCI-000803"],"nist":"IA-7 Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/login.defs\" and ensure the following line\nappears:\n\nENCRYPT_METHOD SHA512\n\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"In \"/etc/login.defs\", add or correct the following line to\nensure the system will use SHA-512 as the hashing algorithm:\n\nENCRYPT_METHOD SHA512","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*ENCRYPT_METHOD[\\s]+SHA512[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*ENCRYPT_METHOD[\\s]+SHA512[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38645":{"vuln_num":"V-38645","rule_title":"The system default umask in /etc/login.defs must be 077.","vuln_discuss":"The umask value influences the permissions assigned to files when they\nare created. A misconfigured umask value could result in files with excessive\npermissions that can be read and/or written to by unauthorized users.","gid":"V-38645","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50446r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000345","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Verify the \"umask\" setting is configured correctly in the\n\"/etc/login.defs\" file by running the following command:\n\n# grep -i \"umask\" /etc/login.defs\n\nAll output must show the value of \"umask\" set to 077, as shown in the below:\n\n# grep -i \"umask\" /etc/login.defs\nUMASK 077\n\n\nIf the above command returns no output, or if the umask is configured\nincorrectly, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To ensure the default umask controlled by \"/etc/login.defs\" is\nset properly, add or correct the \"umask\" setting in \"/etc/login.defs\" to\nread as follows:\n\nUMASK 077","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*UMASK[\\s]+([^#\\s]*)/\n","PASS -- 077 should eq \"077\"\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/login.defs content should match /^[\\s]*UMASK[\\s]+([^#\\s]*)/\nPASS -- 077 should eq \"077\"\n"},"V-38494":{"vuln_num":"V-38494","rule_title":"The system must prevent the root account from logging in from serial\nconsoles.","vuln_discuss":"Preventing direct root login to serial port interfaces helps ensure\naccountability for actions taken on the systems using the root account.","gid":"V-38494","group_title":"SRG-OS-000109","rule_id":"SV-50295r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000028","cci_ref":["CCI-000770"],"nist":"IA-2 (5) Rev_4","check_content":"To check for serial port entries which permit root login, run\nthe following command:\n\n# grep '^ttyS[0-9]' /etc/securetty\n\nIf any output is returned, then root login over serial ports is permitted.\nIf root login over serial ports is permitted, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To restrict root logins on serial ports, ensure lines of this\nform do not appear in \"/etc/securetty\":\n\nttyS0\nttyS1\n\nNote:  Serial port entries are not limited to those listed above.  Any lines\nstarting with \"ttyS\" followed by numerals should be removed","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/securetty content should not match /^ttyS[0-9]+$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/securetty content should not match /^ttyS[0-9]+$/\n"},"V-38594":{"vuln_num":"V-38594","rule_title":"The rshd service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"The rsh service uses unencrypted network communications, which means\nthat data from the login session, including passwords and all other information\ntransmitted during the session, can be stolen by eavesdroppers on the network.","gid":"V-38594","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033","rule_id":"SV-50395r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000214","cci_ref":["CCI-000068"],"nist":"AC-17 (2) Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"rsh\" service is disabled in system boot\nconfiguration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"rsh\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"rsh\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"rsh\" --list\nrsh off\nOR\nerror reading information on service rsh: No such file or directory\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"rsh\" service, which is available with the \"rsh-server\"\npackage and runs as a service through xinetd, should be disabled. The \"rsh\"\nservice can be disabled with the following command:\n\n# chkconfig rsh off","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package rsh-server should not be installed\n"},"V-38605":{"vuln_num":"V-38605","rule_title":"The cron service must be running.","vuln_discuss":"Due to its usage for maintenance and security-supporting tasks,\nenabling the cron daemon is essential.","gid":"V-38605","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50406r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000224","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"Run the following command to determine the current status of\nthe \"crond\" service:\n\n# service crond status\n\nIf the service is enabled, it should return the following:\n\ncrond is running...\n\n\nIf the service is not running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"crond\" service is used to execute commands at\npreconfigured times. It is required by almost all systems to perform necessary\nmaintenance tasks, such as notifying root of system activity. The \"crond\"\nservice can be enabled with the following commands:\n\n# chkconfig crond on\n# service crond start","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package cronie should be installed\n","PASS -- Service crond runlevels 2 should be enabled\n","PASS -- Service crond runlevels 3 should be enabled\n","PASS -- Service crond runlevels 4 should be enabled\n","PASS -- Service crond runlevels 5 should be enabled\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package cronie should be installed\nPASS -- Service crond runlevels 2 should be enabled\nPASS -- Service crond runlevels 3 should be enabled\nPASS -- Service crond runlevels 4 should be enabled\nPASS -- Service crond runlevels 5 should be enabled\n"},"V-38502":{"vuln_num":"V-38502","rule_title":"The /etc/shadow file must be owned by root.","vuln_discuss":"The \"/etc/shadow\" file contains the list of local system accounts\nand stores password hashes. Protection of this file is critical for system\nsecurity. Failure to give ownership of this file to root provides the\ndesignated owner with access to sensitive information which could weaken the\nsystem security posture.","gid":"V-38502","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50303r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000033","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check the ownership of \"/etc/shadow\", run the command:\n\n$ ls -l /etc/shadow\n\nIf properly configured, the output should indicate the following owner:\n\"root\"\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"To properly set the owner of \"/etc/shadow\", run the command:\n\n# chown root /etc/shadow","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\n","PASS -- File /etc/shadow uid should cmp == 0\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/shadow should exist\nPASS -- File /etc/shadow uid should cmp == 0\n"},"V-38577":{"vuln_num":"V-38577","rule_title":"The system must use a FIPS 140-2 approved cryptographic hashing\nalgorithm for generating account password hashes (libuser.conf).","vuln_discuss":"Using a stronger hashing algorithm makes password cracking attacks\nmore difficult.","gid":"V-38577","group_title":"SRG-OS-000120","rule_id":"SV-50378r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000064","cci_ref":["CCI-000803"],"nist":"IA-7 Rev_4","check_content":"Inspect \"/etc/libuser.conf\" and ensure the following line\nappears in the \"[default]\" section:\n\ncrypt_style = sha512\n\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"In \"/etc/libuser.conf\", add or correct the following line in\nits \"[defaults]\" section to ensure the system will use the SHA-512 algorithm\nfor password hashing:\n\ncrypt_style = sha512","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/libuser.conf content should match /^[\\s]*crypt_style[\\s]+=[\\s]+(?i)sha512[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/libuser.conf content should match /^[\\s]*crypt_style[\\s]+=[\\s]+(?i)sha512[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38584":{"vuln_num":"V-38584","rule_title":"The xinetd service must be uninstalled if no network services\nutilizing it are enabled.","vuln_discuss":"Removing the \"xinetd\" package decreases the risk of the xinetd\nservice's accidental (or intentional) activation.","gid":"V-38584","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50385r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000204","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"If network services are using the xinetd service, this is not\napplicable.\n\nRun the following command to determine if the \"xinetd\" package is installed:\n\n# rpm -q xinetd\n\n\nIf the package is installed, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The \"xinetd\" package can be uninstalled with the following\ncommand:\n\n# yum erase xinetd","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package xinetd should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package xinetd should not be installed\n"},"V-38644":{"vuln_num":"V-38644","rule_title":"The ntpdate service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"The \"ntpdate\" service may only be suitable for systems which are\nrebooted frequently enough that clock drift does not cause problems between\nreboots. In any event, the functionality of the ntpdate service is now\navailable in the ntpd program and should be considered deprecated.","gid":"V-38644","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50445r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000265","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"ntpdate\" service is disabled in system\nboot configuration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"ntpdate\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"ntpdate\" service has either not been installed,\nor has been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"ntpdate\" --list\n\"ntpdate\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"ntpdate\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service ntpdate status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\nntpdate is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The ntpdate service sets the local hardware clock by polling NTP\nservers when the system boots. It synchronizes to the NTP servers listed in\n\"/etc/ntp/step-tickers\" or \"/etc/ntp.conf\" and then sets the local hardware\nclock to the newly synchronized system time. The \"ntpdate\" service can be\ndisabled with the following commands:\n\n# chkconfig ntpdate off\n# service ntpdate stop","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package ntpdate should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package ntpdate should not be installed\n"},"V-38640":{"vuln_num":"V-38640","rule_title":"The Automatic Bug Reporting Tool (abrtd) service must not be running.","vuln_discuss":"Mishandling crash data could expose sensitive information about\nvulnerabilities in software executing on the local machine, as well as\nsensitive information from within a process's address space or registers.","gid":"V-38640","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096","rule_id":"SV-50441r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000261","cci_ref":["CCI-000382"],"nist":"CM-7 b Rev_4","check_content":"To check that the \"abrtd\" service is disabled in system boot\nconfiguration, run the following command:\n\n# chkconfig \"abrtd\" --list\n\nOutput should indicate the \"abrtd\" service has either not been installed, or\nhas been disabled at all runlevels, as shown in the example below:\n\n# chkconfig \"abrtd\" --list\n\"abrtd\" 0:off 1:off 2:off 3:off 4:off 5:off 6:off\n\nRun the following command to verify \"abrtd\" is disabled through current\nruntime configuration:\n\n# service abrtd status\n\nIf the service is disabled the command will return the following output:\n\nabrtd is stopped\n\n\nIf the service is running, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The Automatic Bug Reporting Tool (\"abrtd\") daemon collects and\nreports crash data when an application crash is detected. Using a variety of\nplugins, abrtd can email crash reports to system administrators, log crash\nreports to files, or forward crash reports to a centralized issue tracking\nsystem such as RHTSupport. The \"abrtd\" service can be disabled with the\nfollowing commands:\n\n# chkconfig abrtd off\n# service abrtd stop","impact":"0.3","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- System Package abrt should not be installed\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- System Package abrt should not be installed\n"},"V-38491":{"vuln_num":"V-38491","rule_title":"There must be no .rhosts or hosts.equiv files on the system.","vuln_discuss":"Trust files are convenient, but when used in conjunction with the\nR-services, they can allow unauthenticated access to a system.","gid":"V-38491","group_title":"SRG-OS-000248","rule_id":"SV-50292r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000019","cci_ref":["CCI-001436"],"nist":"AC-17 (8) Rev_4","check_content":"The existence of the file \"/etc/hosts.equiv\" or a file named\n\".rhosts\" inside a user home directory indicates the presence of an Rsh trust\nrelationship.\nIf these files exist, this is a finding.","fix_text":"The files \"/etc/hosts.equiv\" and \"~/.rhosts\" (in each user's\nhome directory) list remote hosts and users that are trusted by the local\nsystem when using the rshd daemon. To remove these files, run the following\ncommand to delete them from any location.\n\n# rm /etc/hosts.equiv\n\n\n\n$ rm ~/.rhosts","impact":"0.7","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /root/^\\.(r|s)hosts$ should not exist\n","PASS -- Command: `find /home -regex .\\*/\\^\\\\.\\(r\\|s\\)hosts\\$ -type f  -maxdepth 1` stdout should be empty\n","PASS -- File /etc/^s?hosts\\.equiv$ should not exist\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /root/^\\.(r|s)hosts$ should not exist\nPASS -- Command: `find /home -regex .\\*/\\^\\\\.\\(r\\|s\\)hosts\\$ -type f  -maxdepth 1` stdout should be empty\nPASS -- File /etc/^s?hosts\\.equiv$ should not exist\n"},"V-38674":{"vuln_num":"V-38674","rule_title":"X Windows must not be enabled unless required.","vuln_discuss":"Unnecessary services should be disabled to decrease the attack surface\nof the system.","gid":"V-38674","group_title":"SRG-OS-000248","rule_id":"SV-50475r1_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000290","cci_ref":["CCI-001436"],"nist":"AC-17 (8) Rev_4","check_content":"To verify the default runlevel is 3, run the following command:\n\n# grep initdefault /etc/inittab\n\nThe output should show the following:\n\nid:3:initdefault:\n\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","fix_text":"Setting the system's runlevel to 3 will prevent automatic startup\nof the X server. To do so, ensure the following line in \"/etc/inittab\"\nfeatures a \"3\" as shown:\n\nid:3:initdefault:","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed"],"message":["PASS -- File /etc/inittab content should match /^[\\s]*id:3:initdefault:[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- File /etc/inittab content should match /^[\\s]*id:3:initdefault:[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38539":{"vuln_num":"V-38539","rule_title":"The system must be configured to use TCP syncookies when experiencing\na TCP SYN flood.","vuln_discuss":"A TCP SYN flood attack can cause a denial of service by filling a\nsystem's TCP connection table with connections in the SYN_RCVD state.\nSyncookies can be used to track a connection when a subsequent ACK is received,\nverifying the initiator is attempting a valid connection and is not a flood\nsource. This feature is activated when a flood condition is detected, and\nenables the system to continue servicing valid connection requests.","gid":"V-38539","group_title":"SRG-OS-000142","rule_id":"SV-50340r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000095","cci_ref":["CCI-001095"],"nist":"SC-5 (2) Rev_4","check_content":"The status of the \"net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies\" kernel parameter\ncan be queried by running the following command:\n\n$ sysctl net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies\n\nThe output of the command should indicate a value of \"1\". If this value is\nnot the default value, investigate how it could have been adjusted at runtime,\nand verify it is not set improperly in \"/etc/sysctl.conf\".\n\n$ grep net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies /etc/sysctl.conf\n\nIf the correct value is not returned, this is a finding. ","fix_text":"To set the runtime status of the \"net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies\"\nkernel parameter, run the following command:\n\n# sysctl -w net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies=1\n\nIf this is not the system's default value, add the following line to\n\"/etc/sysctl.conf\":\n\nnet.ipv4.tcp_syncookies = 1","impact":"0.5","profile_name":"Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 Security Technical Implementation Guide","profile_shasum":"d09381ba409b13892b91276de23b09d600f091cb66ff75b644d294cbbee9fc9b","status":["passed","passed","passed"],"message":["PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies value should not be nil\n","PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies value should eq 1\n","PASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies[\\s]*=[\\s]*1[\\s]*$/\n"],"compliance_status":"NotAFinding","finding_details":"All Automated tests passed for the control \n\n PASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies value should not be nil\nPASS -- Kernel Parameter net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies value should eq 1\nPASS -- File /etc/sysctl.conf content should match /^[\\s]*net.ipv4.tcp_syncookies[\\s]*=[\\s]*1[\\s]*$/\n"},"V-38529":{"vuln_num":"V-38529","rule_title":"The system must not accept IPv4 source-routed packets by default.","vuln_discuss":"Accepting source-routed packets in the IPv4 protocol has few\nlegitimate uses. It should be disabled unless it is absolutely required.","gid":"V-38529","group_title":"SRG-OS-999999","rule_id":"SV-50330r2_rule","rule_ver":"RHEL-06-000089","cci_ref":["CCI-000366"],"nist":"CM-6 b Rev_4","check_content":"The status of the \"net.ipv4.conf.default.accept_source_route\"\nkernel parameter can be queried by running the following command:\n\n$ sysctl net.ipv4.conf.default.accept_source_route\n\nThe output of the command should indicate a value of \"0\". If this value is\nnot the default value, investigate 